hanes: A Study|location=Oxford and New York|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=1933}}\n* {{cite book| last = Platter| first = Charles|title = Aristophanes and the Carnival of Genres| year = 2006| publisher = JHUP|isbn = 978-0-8018-8527-3 }}\n* G. M. Sifakis ''[https://www.jstor.org/stable/632156 The Structure of Aristophanic Comedy]'' The Journal of Hellenic Studies, Vol. 112, 1992 (1992), pp.&nbsp;123\u2013142 {{doi|10.2307/632156}}\n* {{cite book|last=Taaffe|first=L. K.|title=Aristophanes and Women|location=London and New York|publisher=Routledge|year=1993}}\n* {{cite book|last=Ussher|first=Robert Glenn|title=Aristophanes|location=Oxford|publisher=Clarendon Press|year=1979}}\n* Van Steen, Gonda. 2000 [http://press.princeton.edu/titles/6874.html ''Venom in Verse: Aristophanes in Modern Greece.''] Princeton University Press.\n* [https://www.jstor.org/pss/1561948 Jstor.org], The American Journal of Philology, 1996.\n* [http://dialnet.unirioja.es/servlet/articulo?codigo=1091777 Life, death and Aristophanes' concept of Eros in Saul Bellow's \"Ravelstein\".]\n\n==Further reading==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061007212611/http://etext.library.adelaide.edu.au/a/aristophanes/ The Eleven Comedies (in translation)] at the University of Adelaide Library\n* {{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/comoediaequaesup01aris |title=Comoediae quae supersunt cum perditarum fragmentis |language=Latin |author=Aristophanes |last2=Holden |first2=Hubert Ashton |publisher=Cantabrigia |year=1868}}\n* {{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/ScholiaGraecaInAristophanem |title=Scholia graeca in Aristophanem'' |editor-last=D\u00fcbner |editor-first=Friedrich |publisher= Parisiis Editore |year=1883 |orig-year=1855}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikisource author}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons|Aristofane}}\n{{Library resources box |by=yes |onlinebooks=yes |others=yes |about=yes |label=Aristophanes\n  |viaf= |lccn= |lcheading= |wikititle= }}\n\n* {{Internet Archive author}}\n* {{Gutenberg author |id=965 | name=Aristophanes}}\n* {{FadedPage|id=Aristophanes|name=Aristophanes|author=yes}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=1594}}\n* {{IMdb name}}\n\n{{Aristophanes Plays}}\n{{Ancient Greece topics}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Aristophanes}}\n[[Category:440s BC births]]\n[[Category:380s BC deaths]]\n[[Category:4th-century BC Athenians]]\n[[Category:4th-century BC writers]]\n[[Category:5th-century BC Athenians]]\n[[Category:5th-century BC writers]]\n[[Category:Ancient Athenians]]\n[[Category:Ancient Greek dramatists and playwrights]]\n[[Category:Ancient Greek satirists]]\n[[Category:Aristophanes| ]]\n[[Category:Old Comic poets]]\n[[Category:Writers of lost works]]\n", "name_user": "39.37.202.153", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Did the same birth and death dates issue)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aristophanes"}
{"title_page": "Skechers (song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Skechers\n| type       = single\n| cover      = DripReport - Skechers.png\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Original cover\n| artist     = DripReport\n| released   = January 12, 2020\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   =\n| genre      = <!-- Please source genres -->\n| length     = {{duration|m=1|s=46}}\n| label      = [[Arista Records|Arista]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|Haseeb Ahmad|Julian Hecker}}\n| producer   = OuhBoy\n| prev_title = \n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       =\n}}\n\n\"'''Skechers'''\" is a song by YouTube [[content creation|content creator]] DripReport. The track was released on January 12, 2020, and was produced by Ouhboy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/128253599|title=Skechers / DripReport|via=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]}}</ref>\n\nThe track is DripReport's first single, and is also his first charting single.\n\n== Background ==\nMost of the song's success can be attributed to social media app [[TikTok]], where over one and a half million videos have been made with the song.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tiktok.com/music/Skechers-6788456091559676678?lang=en|title=Skechers created by DripReport {{!}} Popular songs on TikTok}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-features/tiktok-quarantine-coronavirus-hype-house-sway-house-969092/|title=Amid Coronavirus Fears, TikTok Collab Houses Still Going Strong }}</ref>\n\n== Composition ==\n\"Skechers\" is a [[Trap music|trap]] and [[pop rap]] song. It has a length of one minute and 46 seconds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/skechers/1495358864?i=1495358869|title=Skechers - Single by DripReport}}</ref> It was written by DripReport and OuhBoy, who the latter also produced the song.\n\nThe song is written in the key of [[D-flat major]] with a [[tempo]] of 100 beats per minute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tunebat.com/Info/Skechers-DripReport/4z2JaAVPemYJhFKm7e32RA|title=Key & BPM for Skechers by DripReport {{!}} Tunebat|website=tunebat.com|access-date=March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"Skechers\" has charted in countries including New Zealand, Norway, UK, Australia, Ireland, Sweden, Switzerland, Germany and Canada.\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n| 47\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders Tip|6|artist=DripReport|song=Skechers|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|5|artist=DripReport|song=Skechers|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canada ([[Canadian Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/canadian-hot-100/2020-04-18|title=Canadian Hot 100: April 18, 2020|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 40\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|46|year=2020|week=15|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/?semaine=15?&annee=2020&categorie=Top%20Singles|title=Top Singles (Week 15, 2020)|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique]]|language=French|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n| 66\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|41|songid=1969861|artist=DripReport|song=Skechers|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020|note=<ref>https://www.offiziellecharts.de/suche?artist_search=DripReport&do_search=do</ref>}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Ireland ([[Iris