{"title_page": "Nandy (singer)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{short description|Tanzanian singer and songwriter}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Nandy\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Nandy dodoma fiesta nov 2017.jpg\n| alt              = Picture of Nandy\n| caption          = Nandy on stage at the Fiesta Concert in [[Dodoma, Tanzania]], 2017\n| birth_name       = Faustina Charles Mfinanga\n| birth_date       = {{birth date|1992|11|9}} (age {{age|1992|11|9}})\n| birth_place      = [[Mawenzi]], [[Moshi, Tanzania]]\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n*Tanzanian Artist\n* Singer\n* Songwriter\n* Activist\n*actress\n}}<!--Please do not add to this list without first discussing your proposal on the talk page. -->\n| years_active     = 2013\u2013present\n| module           = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed        = yes\n| background   = solo_singer\n| genre        = {{flatlist|\n* [[Afro pop | Bongo flava]]\n}}\n| instrument   = Vocals\n| label        = {{flatlist|\n* Epic Tanzania|Epic Tanzania\n}}\n| associated_acts     = {{flatlist|\n* Aslay \n* Madee\n* Mr. Blue\n* Bright\n* Chege\n* J Melody\n}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Nandy''' (born November 9, 1992) is a [[Demographics of Tanzania|Tanzanian]] singer and songwriter. She won the [[All Africa Music Awards]] in the best female artist in East Africa category in 2017.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.musicinafrica.net/magazine/afrima-2017-full-list-winners|title=AFRIMA 2017: Full list of winners|date=November 13, 2017|work=Music in Africa|access-date=12 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.azaniapost.com/entertainment/bongo-flava-ali-kiba-nandy-win-awards-at-afrima-in-nigeria-h9093.html|title=Bongo Flava: Ali Kiba, Nandy win awards at AFRIMA in Nigeria|last=Azaniapost|work=Azaniapost|access-date=12 May 2018|language=tr}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nNandy was born in [[Moshi, Tanzania]] to Mary Charles, a tailor and Charles Mfinanga, a mechanic. The name Nandy is shortened from her real name Nandera. She started performing at a very tender age. At 5 years of age, she was an active member of her Sunday school choir at KKKT [[Lutheran church]] in Moshi. She attended Mawenzi Primary School and later joined Lomwe High School where she became the head of School choir. After high school, she joined [[College of Business Education]] (CBE), [[Dar es Salaam]], Tanzania.\n\n==Career==\n===Tanzania House of Talent===\nHer career in music kicked off when a common friend introduced her to Ruge Mutahaba, CEO of Tanzania House of Talent (THT). This is where she met Emma the Boy, who produced her first mainstream single, ''Nagusagusa''.The song became a huge hit within a week of its release. \n\nIn early 2016 she participated in a singing competition ''Tecno own the stage''. The contest featured contestants from all over Africa and during the finals in [[Lagos, Nigeria]], Nandy emerged as the first runner-up. The competition groomed her well music wise, as she gained performance confidence, and also acquired essential knowledge of the music industry from the musical tutors and mentors such as chocolate City's [[M.I Abaga]], [[Yemi Alade]] and Bien of [[Sauti Sol]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/movies/tecno-own-the-stage-29-year-old-wins-25k-recording-deal-id4658851.html|title=29-year-old wins $25K, recording deal|work=pulse.ng|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201602120881.html|title=Tanzania: Heartbreak for Tanzania's Nandy in Lagos|work=allafrica.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018|url-access=subscription }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 she released her hit single ''One Day'' which spear headed her career and gave her a couple of opportunities as she was one of the few artist who participated in Coke Studio Africa in 2017 and later the same year she was nominated in the [[All_Africa_Music_Awards#2017_Edition|All Africa Music Awards]] as best female eastern Africa and won.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.coca-cola.co.ke/cokestudio/home/artists/season05/nandy/|title=MEET THE AFRICAN PRINCESS|work=coca-cola.co.ke|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.coca-colacompany.com/videos/nandy-mane-fitsum-cover-coke-studio-africa-ytgokxzmofrtc|title=Nandy: Mane Fitsum (Cover) \u2013 Coke Studio Africa|work=coca-colacompany.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://celebvibestar.co.ke/aslay-nandy-subalkheri-mpenzi/|title=Aslay \u2013 Subalkheri Mpenzi Ft Nandy|work=celebvibestar.co.ke|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ethiosports.com/2017/09/09/coke-studio-africa-2017-officially-launches-in-ethiopia/|title=Coke Studio Africa 2017 Officially Launches in Ethiopia|work=ethiosports.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thecitizen.co.tz/magazine/thebeat/Nandy-and-AliKiba-shine-at-Afrima/1843792-4190288-al1cfbz/index.html|title=Nandy and AliKiba shine at Afrima|work=thecitizen.co.tz|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mwananchi.co.tz/Makala/Nandy-atamani-kuwa-kama-Beyonce/1597592-3845790-9lst8s/index.html|title=Nandy atamani kuwa kama Beyonce|work=mwananchi.co.tz|language=sw|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n===Goodwill Ambassador===\nShe is currently Tanzania's Goodwill ambassador for UNICEF's water, sanitation and hygiene programme ([[WASH]]) that works in over 100 countries worldwide to improve water and sanitation services, as well as basic hygiene practices. The programme focuses on providing people with clean water and basic toilets.\n==Controversies==\nIn April 2018, Nandy and fellow Tanzanian singer, Billnas were briefly detained by the Tanzanian authorities for sharing what they considered as being indecent or obscene content online.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/news/africa/2018-04-17-popular-tanzanian-singer-arrested-in-latest-internet-crackdown/|title=Popular Tanzanian singer arrested in latest internet crackdown|work=Sunday Times (Johannesburg)|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref> \nShe is has been one of the few singers and also actress on a most viewed series called(huba) and most of the time she has appeared in most listened female artist (Boomplay). Her struggles has made her one the most leading Tanzanian female artist singer to ever been listened and streamed in East Africa. Earlier in April 2020 her fellow singer Billnas proposed to her on a live show which made a lot of buzz and excitement to fans that they never thought they would ever be engaged in such a republic world but it happened. Nandy herself reacted so happy about her fellow singer proposing in front of the audience and promised to fight for her love whatever it takes whether in the bad or good.\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Singles ===\n* I'm Confident (2013)\n* Nagusa gusa (2017)\n* One Day (2017)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://notjustok.com/eastafrica/2017/02/20/nandy-one-day/|title=Nandy \u2013 One Day|work=notjustok.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* Wasikudanye (2017)\n* Kivuruge (2017)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.uplandradiofm.com/2017/11/new-music-nandy-kivuruge.html|title=New Music: Nandy \u2013 Kivuruge|work=uplandradiofm.com|language=sw|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* Ninogeshe (2018)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tooxclusive.com.ng/2018/05/nandy-ninogeshe/|title=Nandy \u2013 Ninogeshe|work=tooxclusive.com.ng|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n*Aibu (2018)  \n*hazipo(2019)\n*haleluya(2019)\n*kiza kinene(2019)\n*kata(2020)\n*na nusu\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award Ceremony\n!Prize\n!Work/Recipient\n!Result\n|-\n|2017\n|[[All Africa Music Awards]]<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/>\n|Best Female Artist East Africa\n|Nandy\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2018\n|AMI Awards Afrika<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://whatshappeningmagazineug.com/ami-awards-afrika-2018-full-nominee-list/|title=AMI Awards Afrika 2018 full nominee list|work=whatshappeningmagazineug.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n|Best Female Newcomer\n|Nandy\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Nandy (singer)}}\n[[Category:Tanzanian singers]]\n[[Category:People from Dar es Salaam]]\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{short description|Tanzanian singer and songwriter}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Nandy\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = Nandy dodoma fiesta nov 2017.jpg\n| alt              = Picture of Nandy\n| caption          = Nandy on stage at the Fiesta Concert in [[Dodoma, Tanzania]], 2017\n| birth_name       = Faustina Charles Mfinanga\n| birth_date       = {{birth date|1992|11|9}} (age {{age|1992|11|9}})\n| birth_place      = [[Mawenzi]], [[Moshi, Tanzania]]\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n*Tanzanian Artist\n* Singer\n* Songwriter\n* Activist\n*actress\n}}<!--Please do not add to this list without first discussing your proposal on the talk page. -->\n| years_active     = 2013\u2013present\n| module           = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed        = yes\n| background   = solo_singer\n| genre        = {{flatlist|\n* [[Afro pop | Bongo flava]]\n}}\n| instrument   = Vocals\n| label        = {{flatlist|\n* Epic Tanzania|Epic Tanzania\n}}\n| associated_acts     = {{flatlist|\n* Aslay \n* Madee\n* Mr. Blue\n* Bright\n* Chege\n* J Melody\n}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Nandy''' (born November 9, 1992) is a [[Demographics of Tanzania|Tanzanian]] singer and songwriter. She won the [[All Africa Music Awards]] in the best female artist in East Africa category in 2017.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.musicinafrica.net/magazine/afrima-2017-full-list-winners|title=AFRIMA 2017: Full list of winners|date=November 13, 2017|work=Music in Africa|access-date=12 May 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.azaniapost.com/entertainment/bongo-flava-ali-kiba-nandy-win-awards-at-afrima-in-nigeria-h9093.html|title=Bongo Flava: Ali Kiba, Nandy win awards at AFRIMA in Nigeria|last=Azaniapost|work=Azaniapost|access-date=12 May 2018|language=tr}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nNandy was born in [[Moshi, Tanzania]] to Mary Charles, a tailor and Charles Mfinanga, a mechanic. The name Nandy is shortened from her real name Nandera. She started performing at a very tender age. At 5 years of age, she was an active member of her Sunday school choir at KKKT [[Lutheran church]] in Moshi. She attended Mawenzi Primary School and later joined Lomwe High School where she became the head of School choir. After high school, she joined [[College of Business Education]] (CBE), [[Dar es Salaam]], Tanzania.\n\n==Career==\n===Tanzania House of Talent===\nHer career in music kicked off when a common friend introduced her to Ruge Mutahaba, CEO of Tanzania House of Talent (THT). This is where she met Emma the Boy, who produced her first mainstream single, ''Nagusagusa''.The song became a huge hit within a week of its release. \n\nIn early 2016 she participated in a singing competition ''Tecno own the stage''. The contest featured contestants from all over Africa and during the finals in [[Lagos, Nigeria]], Nandy emerged as the first runner-up. The competition groomed her well music wise, as she gained performance confidence, and also acquired essential knowledge of the music industry from the musical tutors and mentors such as chocolate City's [[M.I Abaga]], [[Yemi Alade]] and Bien of [[Sauti Sol]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/movies/tecno-own-the-stage-29-year-old-wins-25k-recording-deal-id4658851.html|title=29-year-old wins $25K, recording deal|work=pulse.ng|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201602120881.html|title=Tanzania: Heartbreak for Tanzania's Nandy in Lagos|work=allafrica.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018|url-access=subscription }}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 she released her hit single ''One Day'' which spear headed her career and gave her a couple of opportunities as she was one of the few artist who participated in Coke Studio Africa in 2017 and later the same year she was nominated in the [[All_Africa_Music_Awards#2017_Edition|All Africa Music Awards]] as best female eastern Africa and won.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.coca-cola.co.ke/cokestudio/home/artists/season05/nandy/|title=MEET THE AFRICAN PRINCESS|work=coca-cola.co.ke|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.coca-colacompany.com/videos/nandy-mane-fitsum-cover-coke-studio-africa-ytgokxzmofrtc|title=Nandy: Mane Fitsum (Cover) \u2013 Coke Studio Africa|work=coca-colacompany.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://celebvibestar.co.ke/aslay-nandy-subalkheri-mpenzi/|title=Aslay \u2013 Subalkheri Mpenzi Ft Nandy|work=celebvibestar.co.ke|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ethiosports.com/2017/09/09/coke-studio-africa-2017-officially-launches-in-ethiopia/|title=Coke Studio Africa 2017 Officially Launches in Ethiopia|work=ethiosports.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thecitizen.co.tz/magazine/thebeat/Nandy-and-AliKiba-shine-at-Afrima/1843792-4190288-al1cfbz/index.html|title=Nandy and AliKiba shine at Afrima|work=thecitizen.co.tz|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mwananchi.co.tz/Makala/Nandy-atamani-kuwa-kama-Beyonce/1597592-3845790-9lst8s/index.html|title=Nandy atamani kuwa kama Beyonce|work=mwananchi.co.tz|language=sw|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n===Goodwill Ambassador===\nShe is currently Tanzania's Goodwill ambassador for UNICEF's water, sanitation and hygiene programme ([[WASH]]) that works in over 100 countries worldwide to improve water and sanitation services, as well as basic hygiene practices. The programme focuses on providing people with clean water and basic toilets.\n==Controversies==\nIn April 2018, Nandy and fellow Tanzanian singer, Billnas were briefly detained by the Tanzanian authorities for sharing what they considered as being indecent or obscene content online.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/news/africa/2018-04-17-popular-tanzanian-singer-arrested-in-latest-internet-crackdown/|title=Popular Tanzanian singer arrested in latest internet crackdown|work=Sunday Times (Johannesburg)|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref> \nShe is has been one of the few singers and also actress on a most viewed series called(huba) and most of the time she has appeared in most listened female artist (Boomplay). Her struggles has made her one the most leading Tanzanian female artist singer to ever been listened and streamed in East Africa.                                    Earlier in aprill 2020 her fellow singer billnas proposed to her on a live show which made alot of buzz and excitement to fans that they never thought they would ever be engaged in such a republic world but it happened.Nandy herself reacted so happy about her fellow singer proposing infront of the audience and promised to fight for her love whatever it takes wether in the bad or good.\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Singles ===\n* I'm Confident (2013)\n* Nagusa gusa (2017)\n* One Day (2017)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://notjustok.com/eastafrica/2017/02/20/nandy-one-day/|title=Nandy \u2013 One Day|work=notjustok.com|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* Wasikudanye (2017)\n* Kivuruge (2017)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.uplandradiofm.com/2017/11/new-music-nandy-kivuruge.html|title=New Music: Nandy \u2013 Kivuruge|work=uplandradiofm.com|language=sw|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n* Ninogeshe (2018)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tooxclusive.com.ng/2018/05/nandy-ninogeshe/|title=Nandy \u2013 Ninogeshe|work=tooxclusive.com.ng|accessdate=May 4, 2018}}</ref>\n*Aibu (2018)  \n*hazipo(2019)\n*haleluya(2019)\n*kiza kinene(2019)\n*kata(2020)\n*na nusu\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Award Ceremony\n!Prize\n!Work/Recipient\n!Result\n|-\n|2017\n|[[All Africa Music Awards]]<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref name=\"auto1\"/